sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Client
    participant K8sAPI as K8s API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Webhook as Webhook Server<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Operator as MR Operator<br/>(Reconciler)
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Proxy as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant REST as Registry REST<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant DB as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP

    rect rgb(230, 240, 255)
        Note over User,DB: Flow 1: Model Registry Instance Deployment
        User->>K8sAPI: Create ModelRegistry CR<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+ Bearer Token
        K8sAPI->>Webhook: Validate/Mutate<br/>HTTPS/9443 TLS (cert-manager)
        Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Admitted (migrates OAuth→kube-rbac-proxy)
        K8sAPI-->>User: CR Created
        K8sAPI->>Operator: Reconcile Event
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Deployment, Service,<br/>Route, RBAC, NetworkPolicy<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS SA Token
        K8sAPI-->>Operator: Resources Created
    end

    rect rgb(230, 255, 230)
        Note over User,DB: Flow 2: Model Registry REST API Access (kube-rbac-proxy)
        User->>Router: GET /api/model_registry/v1/...<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS Bearer Token
        Router->>Proxy: Forward Request<br/>HTTPS/8443 TLS (reencrypt)
        Proxy->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>(can user GET services/{name}?)<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS SA Token
        K8sAPI-->>Proxy: Allowed
        Proxy->>REST: Forward Request<br/>HTTP/8080 (localhost, no auth)
        REST->>DB: Query metadata<br/>TCP/5432 Password Auth<br/>(Optional SSL)
        DB-->>REST: Results
        REST-->>Proxy: JSON Response
        Proxy-->>Router: Response
        Router-->>User: JSON Response
    end

    rect rgb(255, 245, 230)
        Note over User,DB: Flow 3: Model Catalog Access
        User->>Router: GET model-catalog API<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS Bearer Token
        Router->>Proxy: Forward Request<br/>HTTPS/8443 TLS (reencrypt)
        Proxy->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>(can user GET services/model-catalog?)<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS SA Token
        K8sAPI-->>Proxy: Allowed
        Proxy->>REST: Forward Request<br/>HTTP/8080 (localhost)
        REST->>DB: Query catalog data<br/>TCP/5432 Password Auth
        DB-->>REST: Results
        REST-->>Proxy: JSON Response
        Proxy-->>Router: Response
        Router-->>User: JSON Response
    end
